article.headline: Prairie View 72, Southern U. 57
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Michael Griffin scored 21 points to lead Prairie View past Southern University 72-57 on Saturday night in the final game of the regular season for both teams. The Panthers (10-21, 7-11 Southwest Athletic) shot 40.8 percent from the field and took a 47-35 rebounding advantage with the help of Duwan Kornegay, who finished with nine points and a game-high 15 rebounds. The win gave Prairie View a No. 7 seed in the SWAC tournament. The Panthers are scheduled to play No. 2 seed Jackson State on Wednesday. Brandon White led the Jaguars (3-15, 4-26) with 14 points while Blake Sanford added 11. Tim Meadows chipped in with 13 points for Prairie View. Southern U. did not qualify for the conference tournament.
